==English==

'''Noun'''

''(Computing, countable)''

'''Assembly language''' is a low-level [[programming language]] used mostly in writing [[operating system]]s, [[hardware]] [[drivers]], and [[video games]]. Assembly language allows direct control of hardware devices.

===Typical Assembly Language instructions===

*MOV AH,2Eh
*INT 21
*CMP BL,CH
*JNE LABEL

===Synonyms===
*[[Assembler]]
*Machine code (Incorrect usage by some programmers)

